1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,280
 First of all, Happy New Year, everyone.

2
00:00:02,280 --> 00:00:03,800
 Happy New Year.

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:05,640
 So lovely to come to Yuen Long.

4
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:09,680
 I think this is the furthest I've traveled during the New Year to Yuen Long.

5
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:15,560
 But it's very lovely to worship with you and seeing new faces, old faces, old friends,

6
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:20,080
 and also seeing the kids growing a lot taller since the last time I was here.

7
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:22,640
 It's really lovely to be here.

8
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:28,880
 So, yeah, hope you are enjoying your family time, your public holiday,

9
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:31,360
 perhaps some Chinese food as well.

10
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:40,280
 So if you don't really celebrate CNY, I hope you enjoy some time off this week as well.

11
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:45,840
 So in case I might be new to some of you, so I'm Jennifer.

12
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:47,040
 I grew up in Hong Kong.

13
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:51,400
 My family is a very traditional Chinese family.

14
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:58,400
 So every year as a kid, CNY is a big thing for my family to celebrate together.

15
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:01,840
 And I am the only Christian of my family.

16
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:04,080
 I'm still the only Christian.

17
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:14,000
 So for my family, they really hold on to the traditions of CNY.

18
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:21,760
 And they believe that following those traditions will bring us blessings and good luck for the whole year.

19
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:29,560
 So growing up, I'm in an environment that my parents would make sure that I only say good things during CNY.

20
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,960
 Maybe there are certain things I can't do.

21
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:35,560
 I can't wash my hair on a certain day and things like that,

22
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:38,400
 which is a little bit interesting to me growing up.

23
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:41,400
 But yeah, this is how I'm raised.

24
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:46,040
 And there is one tradition that I must do every year,

25
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:50,200
 which is on the New Year day, the first day of the CNY,

26
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,280
 I have to, whenever I get up, before I brush my teeth,

27
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:59,000
 I go to my parents' bedroom and I need to say at least three greetings to them.

28
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:03,080
 And until they are satisfied, they will give me a Lai Si.

29
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:05,960
 Yeah, my mom is the one who's strict.

30
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:09,440
 She could reject my blessing and say another one.

31
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:13,960
 And unless she is satisfied, then I will get my Lai Si.

32
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:18,320
 So I'm sure you've heard of this if you were around Hong Kong for a while,

33
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:22,200
 like Gong Hei Fa Choy, wish you get rich,

34
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,840
 and Sun Tai Gin Hong, wish you good health.

35
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:29,600
 These are the common things that we say to one another during CNY.

36
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:32,960
 And also for the married couple,

37
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:36,560
 that they will give Lai Si to the unmarried one,

38
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:39,160
 which is a sign of blessing as well.

39
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:42,720
 So that says that during CNY,

40
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:46,480
 the whole city will go around to bless one another

41
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:48,880
 or to get blessings from other things.

42
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:53,840
 And you will see maybe culturally that they will go for fortune telling

43
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,720
 or go to the temples as well.

44
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:58,440
 So this year, this time of the year,

45
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:02,600
 that the whole city is chasing the blessings from one another

46
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,400
 or from different things.

47
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:08,120
 And perhaps you don't really observe the CNY tradition,

48
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:13,760
 but the tension of how do we get blessings is actually everywhere.

49
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:17,400
 For example, there are always different myths in different cities

50
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,480
 that how we can get blessed.

51
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:22,680
 Let me show you the picture when I was in Rome,

52
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,240
 that the famous fountain, Trivia Fountain,

53
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:29,480
 that in fact, every day there are many tourists

54
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:31,840
 who toss the coins in the fountain.

55
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,800
 Hopefully they get blessed.

56
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,480
 And if you don't know,

57
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:38,760
 like each day they cleared from the bottom of the fountain,

58
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:44,040
 they find 3,000 euros each day by the tourists.

59
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,080
 It's amazing.

60
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:49,320
 So you see how people really want to get blessed.

61
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,040
 And if you have traveled to Europe,

62
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:54,320
 they will tell you there are certain ways you cross the bridge

63
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:58,400
 or you touch a random statue that you will get blessed.

64
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,080
 And in fact, that happened in Vatican as well.

65
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:06,960
 I was told that if you touch, I think, the right foot of Peter's statue,

66
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,000
 that you will get blessed.

67
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:12,960
 And I'm like, it doesn't hurt to do that,

68
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:19,080
 but is this really how we get blessed as Christians?

69
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:22,640
 So today we will look into the scripture later,

70
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:25,400
 but perhaps let's ask ourselves some questions

71
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,320
 around when we are at the timing

72
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:30,840
 that everyone is trying to get blessed in the city,

73
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:35,400
 that how should we approach blessings as Christians?

74
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:39,520
 And what's the difference between God's blessings

75
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:43,360
 and "lai si" or saying "gong hei fat choy" to each other?

76
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:49,520
 And more importantly, how do we dwell in the blessing of God?

77
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:53,360
 So today we will look into some scripture,

78
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:57,680
 but in fact, like the theme of blessing is everywhere in the Bible.

79
00:04:57,680 --> 00:05:02,200
 And as a church, we've just gone through the series of Beatitude

80
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,600
 that we look into Jesus' blessing for us.

81
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:09,240
 And in Genesis, we see blessing everywhere as well.

82
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:12,680
 It says God blessing Noah and his family,

83
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:17,760
 blessing Abraham and how the blessing passed from generations to generations.

84
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:21,840
 And so we see that God does bless people.

85
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:24,240
 God does want to bless us.

86
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:29,160
 So today we will look into a very, perhaps a very famous blessing in the Bible

87
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,520
 to see how God bless people

88
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:39,200
 and how we can reflect on how we approach God's blessings as God's people today.

89
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:43,320
 So we will look into the preceding blessing in Numbers chapter 6.

90
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:48,520
 Let me give a little bit of context before we look into the passage itself.

91
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:53,120
 So at the point we reach Numbers,

92
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:56,800
 Abraham's descendants has grown into a nation.

93
00:05:56,800 --> 00:06:01,440
 In that sense, his promise to Abraham has actually fulfilled

94
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:05,120
 and at the same time, they're not just one family unit,

95
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:10,720
 but a whole nation, many, many, many families staying together.

96
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,680
 So it was way more complicated

97
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:20,240
 in terms of how does following God look like as a nation, as such a big group of people.

98
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:26,160
 And God has anointed Moses to lead Israel out of Egypt.

99
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:32,480
 And he has given Moses, through Moses, he has given Israel a very detailed law

100
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:37,560
 in how they should live as a people of God, as a society.

101
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:44,520
 So in here, chapter 6, it includes God's blessing to the congregation of people.

102
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:49,920
 And this is how the priest bless the people as well,

103
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:53,920
 if you are Jewish or for the Jewish people.

104
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:59,800
 And some Christian pastors actually use this passage as well to do the benediction,

105
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:06,520
 which means it is really a passage widely used for blessing God's people.

106
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:13,200
 And more importantly, the language itself is instructed by God himself.

107
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:18,600
 So in fact, God is saying, if I am to bless people, this is what it looks like.

108
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:22,920
 So let's go through the passage together.

109
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:27,240
 Numbers chapter 6, verses 22 to 27.

110
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:31,360
 The Lord said to Moses, tell Aaron and his sons,

111
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:35,040
 this is how you are to bless the Israelites.

112
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:39,280
 Say to them, the Lord bless you and keep you.

113
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:44,400
 The Lord makes his face shine on you and be gracious to you.

114
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:49,280
 The Lord turn his face towards you and give you peace.

115
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:55,760
 So they will put my name on the Israelites and I will bless them.

116
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:59,440
 I think many of us are quite familiar with this passage,

117
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:03,880
 as there is a whole worship song derived from this passage.

118
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:07,400
 But have we wondered what does the individual words mean?

119
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,640
 What does all the verbs mean?

120
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:11,840
 What does it mean to bless, to keep?

121
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:17,760
 And perhaps what does it mean if God makes his face shine upon you?

122
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:20,080
 Have we thought about that?

123
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:23,880
 And today we will break down these words today, word by word,

124
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:27,400
 so that we can reflect together as a people of God,

125
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:31,120
 how God's blessing means to us.

126
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,680
 Are we ready?

127
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:34,520
 Yes? Wonderful.

128
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:36,600
 So let's start with the first one.

129
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:39,160
 The Lord bless you and keep you.

130
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:46,000
 So bless and keep might be a broader term that we use in our day-to-day conversation as well.

131
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,080
 And let's start with bless.

132
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:52,640
 Bless is also a very broad term in general,

133
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:57,640
 but it has a quite specific meaning and content in the Old Testament.

134
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:05,080
 So in Old Testament, usually it's referring to God blesses people by giving them children,

135
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:13,320
 property, land, the product of the land, good health, and also presence.

136
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,800
 So there are different ways that God bless.

137
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:21,760
 But if we think about it, the blessing is actually related to his promise.

138
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:24,280
 Let's take Abraham as an example.

139
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:30,840
 God has promised to Abraham that he will make him into a great nation.

140
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,840
 But at that time, Abraham did not have any descendants yet.

141
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:42,160
 And so the challenge Abraham was facing was actually barrenness, famine,

142
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:45,400
 and threats that potentially killed the whole family.

143
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:50,160
 So God's blessings to Abraham was around giving him the descendants.

144
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,640
 This is very important.

145
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:57,960
 And also they will live and the descendants will live so that his promise will be fulfilled.

146
00:09:57,960 --> 00:10:03,160
 And now in the book of Numbers, apparently they have grown into a nation,

147
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:07,760
 which means that the promise of God was fulfilled already.

148
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:11,640
 And God has delivered them from the threat of Egypt

149
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:17,640
 and also provided and protected them in their journey in the wilderness so far.

150
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:23,320
 And God's promise to them at that point is to lead them into the promised land.

151
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:27,640
 So there is a sense of anticipating into the land.

152
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:32,200
 So the blessing in the book of Numbers is related to their descendants,

153
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:36,000
 to fruitful lands, to good health, to long life,

154
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:41,600
 to protection from enemies and God's presence being with them.

155
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:45,680
 That says God does bless in a tangible way.

156
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:50,800
 We can hear that like the fruits of the land, the land itself is a very tangible way

157
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,360
 how God bless people.

158
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:58,360
 He provides for them and he protects them in different situations they face.

159
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:02,840
 And same to us today, our God is the same God

160
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:06,760
 who provides and who bless in a tangible way.

161
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,880
 Perhaps it looks different than going into a promised land

162
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:12,600
 or having manna in the wilderness.

163
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:16,720
 But across these years, I've heard so many testimonies

164
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:21,560
 from our brothers and sisters that God provides financially,

165
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:27,920
 that God gives children, that God heals the sickness among us,

166
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:32,880
 and also bringing families to reunion in many, many different ways.

167
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:40,640
 So let us be reminded that God is a God who blesses in tangible ways.

168
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:44,560
 Not sure what you are going through today, in what circumstances,

169
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,960
 or you're waiting for a blessing from God,

170
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:51,520
 but may this be an encouragement to you that God still does that.

171
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:56,920
 God still blesses in many, many different ways.

172
00:11:56,920 --> 00:12:03,160
 And to unpack God's blessings further, let's look at the word "keep" as well.

173
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:07,480
 The word is usually used in a sense of watching over,

174
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:11,400
 preserving, sustaining, and protection,

175
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:15,880
 which is a blessing very needed by Israel at that time.

176
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:19,600
 They were on the way to enter into the promised land.

177
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:25,200
 If we think about it, the challenge and the threats are all over the place.

178
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:28,520
 First of all, in the wilderness, where do they find food?

179
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,960
 So God protected them and provided them in a way that

180
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:35,480
 manna would fall from the sky and they just need to collect them

181
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:39,080
 and follow God's instructions by taking them.

182
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:44,240
 And also, there's such a large group of people wandering around in the wilderness.

183
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,960
 So what would the people think?

184
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:49,360
 What would the people who live around that area think?

185
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,520
 They probably see them as a big threat,

186
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:54,600
 that, "Oh, are they taking our land? Are they fighting us?"

187
00:12:54,600 --> 00:13:01,520
 Which means attack can come anytime, anywhere, as they are in the wilderness.

188
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:06,160
 And they definitely need God's protection in that sense.

189
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,840
 And more importantly, they are to conquer the promised land,

190
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:13,240
 which means there will be four walls involved,

191
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:20,520
 and they need God's protection even more in that sense.

192
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:25,920
 But this is only the external threats that they are facing.

193
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:31,280
 But at the same time, there is an aspect of internal threat as well,

194
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:37,280
 that they will and they are constantly facing the temptation of disobeying God,

195
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:43,560
 turn to other gods, or complaining against God's protection.

196
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:48,880
 And there were incidents where God wants to literally kill them all on the spot.

197
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:54,520
 So there is another layer of the meaning of this word, "keep."

198
00:13:54,520 --> 00:14:02,560
 Across the Old Testament, the word is frequently used in a sense of keeping the covenant.

199
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:08,320
 So we know that God enters into a covenant with Israel,

200
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:13,160
 that he will be the God of Israel and protect them

201
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:18,000
 and bless the generations after generations with Israel.

202
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:27,000
 And by this, with frequently using the "keep" according to the Old Testament,

203
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,840
 Israel is repeatedly called to keep the commandment,

204
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:35,120
 to keep the law of Moses,

205
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:39,480
 and to keep the testimonies and the covenant of the Lord.

206
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:45,760
 So there is a sense of obedience to the revealed instructions in the word itself.

207
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:51,800
 And the biggest purpose of these laws and instructions is to allow Israelites

208
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:57,280
 to know how to follow God, to know how to be God's people,

209
00:14:57,280 --> 00:15:02,120
 and to stay on God's path and not going astray.

210
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:06,840
 And the covenant requires both sides, the promise is from God as well,

211
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:10,640
 as Israel keeps, the Lord keeps as well.

212
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:14,360
 So the Lord says in Deuteronomy 7,

213
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:21,000
 he says, "If you, the Israel, pay attention to these laws and are careful to follow them,

214
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:26,320
 then the Lord your God will keep his covenant of love with you,

215
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:30,000
 as he swore to your ancestors."

216
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,040
 You see from the scripture, it actually reveals the heart of God,

217
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:40,600
 that he really wants to remain in the covenantal relationship with Israel.

218
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:45,240
 And I wonder what it means to us today.

219
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:49,400
 When we live under the new covenant,

220
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:54,080
 the keeping might look a little bit different than following the Mosaic law.

221
00:15:54,080 --> 00:16:00,440
 But God's desire to keep the relationship remains the same to us.

222
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:05,800
 He wants us to follow his path, to follow his leading.

223
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:09,640
 His leading might not look like a pillar of cloud or fire today,

224
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:12,800
 but we have the Holy Spirit in us,

225
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:16,200
 who guides us, who leads us,

226
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:20,520
 who helps us to know Jesus and to follow Jesus,

227
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:24,040
 and to stay on God's path.

228
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:26,040
 So I'm not sure about you,

229
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:32,160
 I do feel that having God to keep me, keep us on the path and not going astray,

230
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:36,360
 is the biggest blessing that God gave me.

231
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:43,440
 So growing up as a Christian, I always wanted God not to give me the option to violate his will.

232
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:48,280
 I want him to just give me the option to follow him so that I don't do anything stupid.

233
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,320
 But apparently that's not the case.

234
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:57,840
 God does give us the free will so that we can follow him and we follow him willfully.

235
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,720
 I think I've shared this around two years ago,

236
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:06,240
 that I sensed that I have a ministry calling since I was in uni.

237
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:12,440
 And I started studying part-time in seminary while working full-time as a paralegal,

238
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:17,720
 because I wasn't quite sure what ministry calling meant to me at that time.

239
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:22,320
 So when I was getting ready, and after some years,

240
00:17:22,320 --> 00:17:26,480
 I felt like, "Oh, I think it's time for me to serve God full-time."

241
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:33,200
 So I made a move, I applied for full-time study in seminary, but I got rejected.

242
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:37,760
 So I was very confused, I really struggled with that rejection.

243
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:45,120
 I thought God has called me, but it felt to me that God did not bless me in that sense

244
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:47,880
 by rejecting me into seminary.

245
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:51,880
 So I was confused, I struggled for a few years,

246
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:57,520
 and then I've decided to take a break, and then I ended up coming to Define.

247
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:04,800
 And so, fast forward to around early 2020, I was praying,

248
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:09,240
 "Oh God, so what do you want me to do? What's my next steps now?"

249
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:11,640
 I was quite impatient in that sense.

250
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:17,840
 So I was trying to make some plans and ask God if that's it, that's his will.

251
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:23,800
 So I made a move, I applied for a role at Define, but I didn't get hired.

252
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:27,200
 So I thought, "Oh yeah, maybe God did not call me to Define."

253
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:33,000
 So I continued, and I was wondering how should I develop my career as well.

254
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:37,960
 So I applied for other paralegal roles, but it was so weird

255
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:41,520
 that I did not offer one single interview.

256
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:45,520
 And with my experience, I thought it's impossible.

257
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,200
 And apparently it was possible.

258
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,120
 So I was like, "What is going on?"

259
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:54,640
 And then until later in 2020, almost the end of 2020,

260
00:18:54,640 --> 00:19:00,440
 Tim approached me and asked me if I wanted to join the pastoral team of Define.

261
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:05,040
 And at that time I was like, "No, I think God said it's not Define."

262
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:12,040
 So I said no immediately to Tim, and he cried.

263
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:18,640
 And then when I got home that day, I was praying,

264
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:25,440
 and then the Holy Spirit was like, "I thought you said you're ready to serve me anytime."

265
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:30,360
 And then I was like, "Oh, that's it? That is it?"

266
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:34,040
 And then I'm like, "Oh no, what have I done?"

267
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:38,920
 But still, I wanted to make sure that I'm held accountable,

268
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:42,120
 so I asked my two close friends to pray with me.

269
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:45,720
 And then after a few days, I reached out to Tim, so I changed my mind.

270
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:48,200
 "Can you send me to JD, please?"

271
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:52,720
 So that's how I ended up being here.

272
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:59,040
 And now, actually it's crazy, this year is my sixth year serving at Define full-time.

273
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:04,880
 And looking back, I was amazed by how God kept me on His path,

274
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:10,080
 even though there are things that I did not expect or I struggled a little bit.

275
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:15,240
 And these five-ish years, I wouldn't say it's a very easy one,

276
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:19,400
 that sometimes I struggle, sometimes I want to give up,

277
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:27,720
 but the Holy Spirit is the one who encourages me and also keeps me on His path.

278
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:30,960
 And it's amazing to see that, looking back,

279
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:36,920
 there are a lot of signs that God stepped in and kept me on His path.

280
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:42,960
 So that said, the reality is there are times that we humans go astray, even for a pastor.

281
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:45,800
 And God knows it already.

282
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:50,080
 Perhaps we can get to know God's heart a little bit more together

283
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,720
 by reading into the next verse,

284
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:58,960
 "The Lord make His face shine on you and be gracious to you."

285
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:01,520
 What an imagery here.

286
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:05,320
 Not sure how you feel after reading this, but when I read this,

287
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:09,960
 I'm like, "Yeah, I think it's a positive thing, but what does it mean?"

288
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:13,960
 So what does it mean by God shining His face on us?

289
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:21,000
 Let's look into the Psalms and see how it was used to understand a little bit further.

290
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:29,920
 So in Psalm 31, it says, "Let your face, God's face, shine on your servant.

291
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:33,120
 Save me in your unfailing love."

292
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:38,240
 And in Psalm 80, it says, "Restore us, O God.

293
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:44,560
 Make your face shine on us, that we may be saved."

294
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:50,760
 We see from the Psalms that when God shines His face on us, we will be saved,

295
00:21:50,760 --> 00:21:56,920
 which means that we can understand this image as God's love and salvation,

296
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,760
 which is God's character as well.

297
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:03,720
 But there is also a more profound meaning in this imagery.

298
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:07,080
 We need to understand what's the opposite of it.

299
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:11,400
 What does it mean if God covers His face?

300
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:16,600
 There are psalmists using this imagery of God hiding His face to represent

301
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:20,320
 God is allowing His people to suffer.

302
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:25,520
 So but why would God allow His people to suffer?

303
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:30,560
 And then we go back to Deuteronomy again, that God actually foresees

304
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:37,560
 Israel will rebel against Him, and this imagery of hiding His face is used there.

305
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:43,760
 Let's read Deuteronomy 31, verses 17 to 18.

306
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:47,840
 "And in that day, I will become angry with them and forsake them.

307
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:52,640
 I will hide my face from them, so they will be destroyed.

308
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:56,440
 Many disasters and calamities will come on them.

309
00:22:56,440 --> 00:23:01,320
 And in that day, they will ask, 'Have not these disasters come on us

310
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:04,560
 because our God is not with us?'

311
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:10,800
 And I will certainly hide my face in that day because of all the wickedness

312
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:15,000
 in turning to other gods."

313
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:20,400
 So we see from this passage that it was Israel's unfaithfulness

314
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:24,400
 which makes God hiding His face.

315
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:31,800
 From this imagery, we see that God shines His face, means He is looking at us.

316
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:39,240
 He is seeing what's going on with us and showing us mercy and grace,

317
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:49,080
 which reveals God's loving character to us, that He loves us no matter what we do,

318
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:55,360
 and He desires for us to remain in the relationship with Him.

319
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:59,600
 And He wants to be close to us.

320
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:04,200
 And that's right, God would like His people to always be obedient,

321
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:11,920
 to always stay on His path, but at the same time, He knows that there are times

322
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:18,040
 humans will be unfaithful, and with this blessing, God is saying to us,

323
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:23,240
 to Israel, that even when there are times we are unfaithful,

324
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:27,920
 He has mercy and compassion when He sees us.

325
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:33,080
 And when He looks and when He shines His face on us,

326
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:39,920
 He will save us even though we are unfaithful in the first place.

327
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:43,960
 So this is essentially the second half of the first,

328
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:49,240
 that the blessing is God is gracious to us.

329
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:55,360
 And the literal meaning of being gracious is a heartfelt inclination of a superior

330
00:24:55,360 --> 00:25:02,080
 to show favor, to show compassion and generosity to one in need.

331
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:09,240
 This emphasize is on the unearned mercy, not a contractual obligation.

332
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:14,720
 So God did have a choice to continue to act according to the covenant,

333
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:21,300
 according to justice, but He will choose to be gracious to us.

334
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:24,720
 And this is who our God is.

335
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:29,360
 I wonder how this blessing speaks to us today,

336
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:36,440
 that even shows us a deeper sense of God, that He wants to remain in our relationship

337
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:39,480
 with His people and with us.

338
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:42,920
 And yes, there are times that we fall, we admit that as human,

339
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:46,720
 we've been there before, that we sin against Him.

340
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,520
 And God knows it already.

341
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:55,420
 And by this blessing, He is telling us that He will choose to be loving

342
00:25:55,420 --> 00:25:58,520
 and to be gracious to us.

343
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:01,960
 This is His character.

344
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:04,160
 And I don't know about you, sometimes we're human,

345
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:07,640
 like Adam and Eve, when we realize we sin against Him,

346
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:14,160
 we want to hide, but God is saying the opposite.

347
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:20,080
 That if that's one of you that you want to hide your face from God,

348
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:24,920
 let this blessing be a reminder that He wants to see us,

349
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,760
 He wants to remain with us.

350
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:35,880
 And we can always go back to our God and Father to ask for His grace.

351
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:41,680
 And as He looks at us, as He shines His faith upon us,

352
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:48,360
 His heart will incline to us and show favor to us.

353
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:51,760
 I wonder how it speaks to you today.

354
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:58,640
 God's blessing is so rich, and there's more, even more from there.

355
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:02,000
 So let's look into the final part of the blessing,

356
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:06,320
 which reveals the heart of God for His people.

357
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:12,280
 The Lord turns His face towards you and gives you peace.

358
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:14,300
 So there's another imagery here.

359
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:20,020
 So what does it mean when God turns His face towards us?

360
00:27:20,020 --> 00:27:28,080
 So by definition in the Old Testament, God lifting His face is an expression.

361
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:33,960
 And it is an expression referring to an appearance of the countenance

362
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:38,640
 of expressive of pleasure and affection.

363
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:44,000
 And functionally, it's equal to a smile.

364
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:47,520
 So in other words, God lifting His face towards us

365
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:54,480
 means that He is accepting us, that He is delight,

366
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:59,080
 and He is pleased with us.

367
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:02,340
 What an imagery here.

368
00:28:02,340 --> 00:28:05,840
 So how about we think of it for a second.

369
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:11,360
 What does it make you feel when you see God is smiling at you

370
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:19,360
 knowing that He is pleased?

371
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:25,080
 If you ask me, perhaps this might be the biggest desire in my life,

372
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:31,720
 that knowing God is pleased by who I am and what I do.

373
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:36,660
 And I would imagine the closest human experience is similar to

374
00:28:36,660 --> 00:28:41,420
 hearing your parents say, "I'm proud of you."

375
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:46,140
 Or someone important to you saying that to you.

376
00:28:46,140 --> 00:28:50,720
 So again, my family is a very stereotyped Asian family.

377
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:54,380
 I seldom hear words of affirmation from them.

378
00:28:54,380 --> 00:28:57,180
 If I don't get an A, I'm not allowed to have dinner,

379
00:28:57,180 --> 00:28:58,180
 and something like that.

380
00:28:58,180 --> 00:29:03,100
 No judgment to my family, but you know, some cultures like that,

381
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:08,660
 it's very hard for us to express our affirmation,

382
00:29:08,660 --> 00:29:12,380
 our approval to the people around us.

383
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:16,020
 But indeed I heard it once, like recently,

384
00:29:16,020 --> 00:29:18,740
 two years ago when I first preached here,

385
00:29:18,740 --> 00:29:22,380
 that I invited my dad, and he was here,

386
00:29:22,380 --> 00:29:26,540
 he left right after the service, but the next day he texted me.

387
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:27,660
 Yes, texted.

388
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:32,620
 He sent me a WhatsApp and said, "I'm proud of you."

389
00:29:32,620 --> 00:29:36,740
 And then I'm like, "Oh, wow, I think this is my first time,

390
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:39,920
 if I remember correctly."

391
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:44,020
 And I think that's a very close feeling to when I know

392
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:46,460
 God is pleased with me.

393
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:48,860
 So I don't know what your upbringing is,

394
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:51,100
 I don't know whether you hear that a lot,

395
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:55,180
 but God is our heavenly Father.

396
00:29:55,180 --> 00:30:00,820
 And He is saying that He is pleased with us.

397
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:08,980
 And He is indeed smiling at us because He is pleased to see us.

398
00:30:08,980 --> 00:30:10,780
 So this is our God.

399
00:30:10,780 --> 00:30:14,420
 This is our God we serve, and He turns His face to us

400
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:19,380
 and gives us this approval smile.

401
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:23,220
 And let's try to sit under this smile today

402
00:30:23,220 --> 00:30:30,580
 and bear that in mind that our heavenly Father is pleased by us.

403
00:30:30,580 --> 00:30:35,420
 And that smile of God brings the ultimate peace.

404
00:30:35,420 --> 00:30:38,180
 And that peace isn't understood in the modern sense

405
00:30:38,180 --> 00:30:40,940
 that it's absence of war or conflict,

406
00:30:40,940 --> 00:30:44,980
 but this peace is described as completeness,

407
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:50,600
 unity and well-being and wholeness.

408
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:53,060
 And more importantly, this peace,

409
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:55,660
 we might know that it's shalom in Hebrew

410
00:30:55,660 --> 00:30:59,340
 that is frequently used in the Old Testament,

411
00:30:59,340 --> 00:31:04,340
 is the result of God's creation in Genesis 1,

412
00:31:04,340 --> 00:31:07,340
 that a world filled with fruitful,

413
00:31:07,340 --> 00:31:13,140
 blessed life in all is wholeness.

414
00:31:13,140 --> 00:31:17,340
 So we see that although God's blessings evolved

415
00:31:17,340 --> 00:31:21,420
 according to people's circumstances of Israel and us

416
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:23,020
 in different seasons,

417
00:31:23,020 --> 00:31:26,100
 but there are things that does not change,

418
00:31:26,100 --> 00:31:31,360
 that God still hope us as human will experience

419
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:37,100
 and restore that shalom He intended for the world.

420
00:31:37,100 --> 00:31:41,460
 So this final verse of blessing contains God's purpose

421
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:46,700
 and God's intention for humanity at all time,

422
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:49,740
 the picture of shalom,

423
00:31:49,740 --> 00:31:55,860
 that human is created to rule over God's creation

424
00:31:55,860 --> 00:32:00,940
 and bring it into the fullness of flourishings.

425
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:06,260
 So this is God's intention for us and for creation.

426
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,940
 And when He looks at that,

427
00:32:07,940 --> 00:32:10,820
 when He looks at the creation,

428
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:16,860
 He gives that approval smile.

429
00:32:16,860 --> 00:32:20,900
 So that reveals God's ultimate heart for us,

430
00:32:20,900 --> 00:32:23,580
 that even after the fall of humanity,

431
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:26,820
 that He still has the same purpose for us,

432
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:28,380
 for Abraham.

433
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:33,100
 He wants all people on the earth will be blessed by Him,

434
00:32:33,100 --> 00:32:37,360
 and for Israel to carry that blessings to all the nations.

435
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:41,900
 And of course, for the death and resurrection of Jesus

436
00:32:41,900 --> 00:32:48,580
 that give us the grace and the restoration of human purpose.

437
00:32:48,580 --> 00:32:51,780
 So today, as His church,

438
00:32:51,780 --> 00:32:58,760
 we are carrying that purpose to restore the shalom to all creations.

439
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:01,260
 So as we celebrate CNY today,

440
00:33:01,260 --> 00:33:07,560
 as we are starting off the year to bless one another,

441
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:13,580
 so how can we carry this blessing to the people around us?

442
00:33:13,580 --> 00:33:16,660
 And here at the Fine, we believe that as Christians,

443
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:19,660
 we are like we have received the grace

444
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:24,860
 and we contribute to that shalom God intends for His creation.

445
00:33:24,860 --> 00:33:30,100
 We can bring God's love, God's hope to the people around us.

446
00:33:30,100 --> 00:33:33,500
 So as we are continuing to celebrate with our families,

447
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:35,100
 with our friends,

448
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:38,200
 maybe we go back to work tomorrow.

449
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,780
 And throughout the times that we communicate

450
00:33:40,780 --> 00:33:44,140
 and spend time with different people,

451
00:33:44,140 --> 00:33:51,980
 let's be present and carry that blessing to the people around us.

452
00:33:51,980 --> 00:33:55,860
 And finally, I want to highlight one more thing to us,

453
00:33:55,860 --> 00:34:02,860
 that in the whole blessing, God's name has repeated three times.

454
00:34:02,860 --> 00:34:05,100
 While grammatically in Hebrew,

455
00:34:05,100 --> 00:34:08,200
 it does not have to repeat in that sense,

456
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:10,960
 but the repetition here emphasize that

457
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:16,400
 the Lord is the source of all blessing.

458
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:20,000
 He does instruct the priest to bless His people.

459
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:25,240
 However, the source of the blessing does not come from the priest

460
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:27,920
 or does not come from the words itself.

461
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:30,040
 The word does not carry magic power

462
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:33,880
 that when we say that, blessing will come.

463
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:41,060
 But God Himself is the source of all the blessing.

464
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:49,800
 And we need to remember that the source of blessing is in Him and Him only.

465
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:53,700
 So the priestly blessing has a very strong sense that

466
00:34:53,700 --> 00:34:59,120
 the blessing comes from our close relationship with God,

467
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:02,080
 that we keep walking on God's path

468
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:07,680
 and God keeps us in the relationship and bless us.

469
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:10,360
 So let's be reminded of that.

470
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:13,460
 And if we look, continue to read the Bible,

471
00:35:13,460 --> 00:35:17,520
 we will see that after Israel entered into the Promised Land,

472
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,360
 they divided the land, they started to own more,

473
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,100
 they have fruit from the land,

474
00:35:22,100 --> 00:35:26,100
 and they were tempted to follow other gods.

475
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:30,140
 And God knew it in the first place and has warned them,

476
00:35:30,140 --> 00:35:34,240
 but they got distracted and chased after different blessing

477
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:37,740
 or idols and forget about God.

478
00:35:37,740 --> 00:35:40,820
 And same to us in the city of Hong Kong.

479
00:35:40,820 --> 00:35:43,560
 There are also different temptations.

480
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:48,600
 In the CNY season, we are seeing different people doing different practice,

481
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:53,960
 maybe going to different gods to get blessings.

482
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:57,940
 And also, it does not only happen in the other gods

483
00:35:57,940 --> 00:36:00,340
 or traditions that we are following.

484
00:36:00,340 --> 00:36:02,340
 In the city of Hong Kong,

485
00:36:02,340 --> 00:36:06,420
 the biggest temptation that we are tempted to own more and more,

486
00:36:06,420 --> 00:36:08,040
 to earn more and more,

487
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:14,620
 and then we rely on what we own and feel content about it.

488
00:36:14,620 --> 00:36:18,760
 So could it be a way that we are tempted to find blessing

489
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:23,360
 in other things in the city of Hong Kong?

490
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:29,300
 So let's be reminded of what our source of blessing is.

491
00:36:29,300 --> 00:36:30,300
 This is our God.

492
00:36:30,300 --> 00:36:34,440
 He always intends to bless His people.

493
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:38,800
 His blessing might not get you rich, to clarify that,

494
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,980
 but He desires to be close to you.

495
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:46,180
 He loves you and He is proud of you.

496
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:51,780
 And His blessing is always enough for us.

497
00:36:51,780 --> 00:36:56,820
 And for that, a relationship always requires both parties to commit.

498
00:36:56,820 --> 00:37:00,900
 It requires us to respond to Him as well.

499
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:04,660
 So let me ask ourselves a question.

500
00:37:04,660 --> 00:37:09,600
 Are we content with God's blessing?

501
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:13,280
 In the culture of always wanting more and more,

502
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:19,520
 are we willing to be content with what God has for us?

503
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:24,980
 When God promised us that He will always be faithful to us,

504
00:37:24,980 --> 00:37:34,560
 are we happy to be faithful to Him and find blessing in Him only?

505
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:41,040
 God never requires us to be perfect, but He wants us to be faithful.

506
00:37:41,040 --> 00:37:45,700
 He wants us to stay close to Him and know Him,

507
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:50,460
 to carry His name to the people around us.

508
00:37:50,460 --> 00:37:55,900
 And that's the way to make Him smile.

509
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:59,900
 So I don't know what resonates with you with this blessing,

510
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:03,860
 and I would like to read the blessing over you again.

511
00:38:03,860 --> 00:38:07,820
 So as we prepare our hearts, may I invite you to stand

512
00:38:07,820 --> 00:38:23,580
 as we receive the blessing from God today.

513
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:29,860
 As we close, as we go about our day, I want us to remember

514
00:38:29,860 --> 00:38:35,700
 that God wants to bless us.

515
00:38:35,700 --> 00:38:38,620
 And He blesses us in different tangible ways.

516
00:38:38,620 --> 00:38:42,260
 He will protect us.

517
00:38:42,260 --> 00:38:46,780
 And no matter what we are going through in our lives,

518
00:38:46,780 --> 00:38:51,660
 no matter even if we want to hide from Him sometimes,

519
00:38:51,660 --> 00:38:54,620
 He wants to be close to us.

520
00:38:54,620 --> 00:38:58,700
 And He wants us to be close to Him.

521
00:38:58,700 --> 00:39:04,140
 And we can always go to our Father in Heaven

522
00:39:04,140 --> 00:39:06,060
 and ask for His grace.

523
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:19,260
 His grace and His love is always available for us as His children.

524
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:23,540
 And also, He is pleased by us.

525
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:29,420
 He is pleased by looking into the individual faces here,

526
00:39:29,420 --> 00:39:32,400
 in all of us.

527
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:43,140
 And He is smiling at us.

528
00:39:43,140 --> 00:39:54,420
 And I want us to receive that today as God's people.

529
00:39:54,420 --> 00:39:58,180
 So let me read over the blessing.

530
00:39:58,180 --> 00:40:09,480
 And let's be comfortable and be in a posture of receiving God's blessing today.

531
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:13,180
 The Lord bless you and keep you.

532
00:40:13,180 --> 00:40:20,140
 The Lord make His face shine on you and be gracious to you.

533
00:40:20,140 --> 00:40:31,640
 The Lord turn His face towards you and give you peace.

534
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:40,240
 Father we thank you that you are a God who always wants to be close to us.

535
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:49,320
 Father, we thank you for this blessing that you give to your people yourselves.

536
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:57,040
 And let us know your heart on how you want to bless us as a people.

537
00:40:57,040 --> 00:41:06,080
 And Lord, we want to be a faithful people to you as well.

538
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:11,120
 As we are going about our week, as we are doing different things,

539
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:17,000
 Lord help us to be reminded of your blessing.

540
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:24,880
 And to be reminded that your blessing is enough for us.

541
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:35,000
 That we want to be a faithful people, to be content with your blessing and with you only.

542
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:43,960
 And Lord, as we go about our week, as we continue to serve you in different ways,

543
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:48,320
 may you show your smile to us.

544
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:56,920
 May we receive and be content with that approval smile on your face.

545
00:41:56,920 --> 00:42:05,160
 We thank you that you are a Father that approves us, that accepts us,

546
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:09,600
 and that is pleased and proud of us.

547
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,200
 And we thank you in Jesus name.

